      <chapter id="773">
        <pagenum>1</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Six factors of self-determination overlap and relate to each other</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Six factors of &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt; overlap and relate to each other&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now that we have explored six factors that affect an individual’s ability to be self-determined, let’s again consider our first guiding question, which asks:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;What does it mean for an adult with LD to be self-determined?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you may have noticed, the six factors seem to overlap and relate with one another. In addition, although we presented them in a particular order, they do not represent a step-by-step process. Factors can be addressed by learners or instructors in any order and/or simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This overlap and integration can be confusing – not only to our learners with LD, but also ourselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Tree_normal.jpg" width="546" height="444" alt="Background image of a tree with the following labels scattered on top of it: Gain Self-Awareness; Learn to Value Yourself; Plan; Be Proactive; Reflect &amp;amp; Readjust; Environment. Graphic title: “Factors Contributing to Self-Determination.”" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
