      <chapter id="775">
        <pagenum>3</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Tree analogy depicts the self-determination model</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Tree analogy depicts the &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt; model&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here we present an example of a model of &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt; attempting to represent how the six factors relate to one another. This model uses a tree analogy to depict&lt;span class="nolink"&gt; self-determinatio&lt;/span&gt;n and the six factors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Citation: This graphic appears in&lt;span class="nolink"&gt; &lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/publications/pdf/L2AProfessionalGuide_final.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Learning to Achieve: A professional’s guide to educating adults with learning disabilities&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.startoolkit.org/assets/files/L2AProfessGuide2010.pdf"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; developed by the National Institute for Literacy.  The graphic is based on Field &amp;amp; Hoffman’s Development of a model for &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt;, 1994. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Self%20Determination%20tree%20graphic.jpg" width="550" height="356" alt="A graphic depiction of the “Self-Determination Model.” Central in image are three stylized trees in green, orange, and blue, left to right. These represent the factors of Plan (green), Be Proactive (orange), and Reflect and Readjust (blue). There are arrows between these factors showing a left-right (green to orange to blue) progression. Under these three trees, ‘in support’, is a solid box with stylized roots coming out of the bottom. In this box are Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself (the roots/base for Plan, Be Proactive and Reflect and Readjust). A double headed arrow shows a back-and-forth relationship between Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself. An arrow stretches around the graphic from Reflect and Readjust to this “root area” of Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself. Another arrow leads to and from this area up and around to Plan. Written vertically on each side of this graphic is the word Environment. Bulleted lists of related elements are listed below each factor (except Environment)." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
        <contentformat>1</contentformat>
        <hidden>0</hidden>
        <timemodified>1463409917</timemodified>
        <importsrc></importsrc>
      </chapter>
      <chapter id="776">
        <pagenum>4</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Roots represent the foundations of self-determination</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Roots represent the foundations of &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="nolink"&gt;Gaining self-awareness&lt;/span&gt; and learning to value yourself - the foundations of &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt; – are shown in this model as the roots of a tree.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/SDtree_wFades1_002_02_190.jpg" width="550" height="356" alt="A graphic depiction of the “Self-Determination Model” with the overall graphic faded back except for the area under the three stylized trees - the solid box with stylized roots coming out of the bottom containing Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself. A double headed arrow shows a back-and-forth relationship between Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself. Bulleted list below Gain Self-Awareness: Understand your needs, preferences, strengths and weaknesses; Become aware of your options; Acknowledge what is critical to you. Bulleted list below Learn to Value Yourself: Accept who you are; Acknowledge and appreciate your unique strengths; Respect responsibilities and rights; Be good to yourself." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
        <contentformat>1</contentformat>
        <hidden>0</hidden>
        <timemodified>1463416758</timemodified>
        <importsrc></importsrc>
      </chapter>
      <chapter id="777">
        <pagenum>5</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Green tree represents planning</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Green tree represents &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;planning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="nolink"&gt;Planning&lt;/span&gt; is represented by the green tree, which is beginning to show buds that have the potential for full bloom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/SD_tree_wFades2_002_02_195.jpg" width="550" height="356" alt="A graphic depiction of the “Self-Determination Model” with the overall graphic faded back except for the Plan area in the upper left. Bulleted list below Plan: Set goals; Determine steps to meet goals; Expect positive results; Embrace your creativity; Practice." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
