      <chapter id="779">
        <pagenum>7</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Blue tree represents reflecting and readjusting</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;Blue tree represents &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;reflecting and readjusting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="nolink"&gt;Reflecting and readjusting&lt;/span&gt; is represented by the blue tree, which is beginning to shed its leaves. To be self-determined, an individual must be able to learn from his or her experiences. For a tree, winter is a time of pause in the growing process, just as reflection and readjustment mean taking time to stop and consider the outcomes of a person’s efforts. This includes deciding what to continue and what to change for next time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/SD_tree_wFades4_002_02_205.jpg" width="550" height="356" alt="A graphic depiction of the “Self-Determination Model” with the overall graphic faded back except for the blue Reflect &amp;amp; Readjust area in the upper right. Bulleted list below Reflect &amp;amp; Readjust: Evaluate differences between actual outcomes/performance and expected outcome/performance; Congratulate success; Readjust for next time." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
        <contentformat>1</contentformat>
        <hidden>0</hidden>
        <timemodified>1463419941</timemodified>
        <importsrc></importsrc>
      </chapter>
      <chapter id="780">
        <pagenum>8</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Environment surrounds the model</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;&lt;span class="nolink"&gt;Environment&lt;/span&gt; surrounds the model&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;environment&lt;/span&gt; is surrounding the entire image. Continuing with the metaphor of a tree, the &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;environment&lt;/span&gt; would be like the sun and soil, elements that feed the tree’s growth. We can structure learning &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;environments&lt;/span&gt; in ways that either promote or inhibit &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;self-determination&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/SD_tree_wFades5_ENVIRO.jpg" width="550" height="356" alt="A graphic depiction of the “Self-Determination Model” with the overall graphic faded back except for the two instances of the word Environment on each side." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
