      <chapter id="781">
        <pagenum>9</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Self-Determination model shows the interrelationship of the six factors</title>
        <content>&lt;h1 class="Subhead"&gt;&lt;span class="nolink"&gt;Self-Determination&lt;/span&gt; model shows the interrelationship of the six factors&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This graphic/analogy provides a good overview of how each of these six factors interrelate to support the process of becoming self-determined. A printer-friendly version of the &lt;span class="nolink"&gt;Self-Determination&lt;/span&gt; Model is provided at the end of this course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This now leads us to our next guiding question and activity. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Self%20Determination%20tree%20graphic.jpg" width="550" height="356" alt="A graphic depiction of the “Self-Determination Model.” Central in image are three stylized trees in green, orange, and blue, left to right. These represent the factors of Plan (green), Be Proactive (orange), and Reflect and Readjust (blue). There are arrows between these factors showing a left-right (green to orange to blue) progression. Under these three trees, ‘in support’, is a solid box with stylized roots coming out of the bottom. In this box are Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself (the roots/base for Plan, Be Proactive and Reflect and Readjust). A double headed arrow shows a back-and-forth relationship between Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself. An arrow stretches around the graphic from Reflect and Readjust to this “root area” of Gain Self-Awareness and Learn to Value Yourself. Another arrow leads to and from this area up and around to Plan. Written vertically on each side of this graphic is the word Environment. Bulleted lists of related elements are listed below each factor (except Environment)." /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
